if you wanna handle the structure of the old projects (projects without Scenes like https://share.catrob.at/app/project/817) please create another function. also, why returning null if `projectScreenshots.length != 0` ?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 26, 0, 51, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ndrnour', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460462505, 'comment_body': '`scene.listFiles(filter)` is already defined as `sceneScreenshots ` in line 136, so please change it to

please replace it with `if (screenshots.isEmpty())`', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 26, 0, 58, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ndrnour', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460463113, 'comment_body': 'again, please no hard coded values, `manual_screenshot.png` is already defined in `StageListener.java` line 106,
could you move it to Constants.java and refactor its usage?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 26, 1, 2, 8, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ndrnour', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460464741, 'comment_body': 'same as line 152, `getParentFile()` returns _abstract pathname of the parent directory named by this abstract pathname, or null if this pathname does not name a parent_ as mentioned in https://developer.android.com/reference/java/io/File#getParentFile() 
I think you need the name of the file, right?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 26, 1, 26, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ndrnour', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460464899, 'comment_body': "what's the reason for changing the width and height? _square aspect ratio!_ as mentioned in the description of https://jira.catrob.at/browse/CATROID-385", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 26, 1, 28, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ndrnour', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460465395, 'comment_body': 'this is misleading, no single change from line 56 on, please revert it and try to avoid Reformat Code (alt+ctrl+L) for the whole file, use it only for the new code. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 26, 1, 35, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ndrnour', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460661568, 'comment_body': "I implemented a new way screenshots are handled. Before we always took the screenshot of the default scene, if there is none, the project thumbnail is empty. From now on we want to use the most recent manual screenshot if available, else the most recent automatic screenshot. Everytime a screenshot is saved, the current screenshot in the project folder is overwritten, so we always have the most recent screenshot.
In this function I'm searching for the Scene thats has the most recent screenshot. (because the screenshot loader has the scenename as parameter). If the projectfolder has a screenshot, I just return null, because we do not need the scenename.
Here I check if the screenshot is available, if I find a screenshot in the project folder i don't need a scenename.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 27, 5, 55, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'juliajulie95', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460662408, 'comment_body': "I need the name of the parent file (the scene where the screenshot is saved in), that's why I take the parent and then the name. How would you do it?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 27, 5, 58, 40, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'juliajulie95', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460665893, 'comment_body': 'There is already a function called getScreenshotFile and my function only gets the Scenename that is used for this function, not the screenshot itself.
Should I still rename it?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 27, 6, 9, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'juliajulie95', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460945969, 'comment_body': 'I see. it would be clearer to me if you rename it to `getScreenshotSceneName`,', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 27, 14, 47, 40, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ndrnour', 'type': 'User'}]
